Install with SeqLib
----------------------
To install Atlas with SeqLib:
- cd SeqLib
- ./configure --> it will check if the requires librairies are installed on the system
- make
- make install
- cd ..
- make

If configure fail:
- check that the librairies zlib, pthread, lzma and bz2
-- To install lzma, run: apt-get install liblzma-dev
-- To install bz2, run: apt-get install libbz2-dev
-- zlib and pthread should be by default installed


Compilation options
----------------------
- make DEBUG=true will allow you to debug ATLAS. Add -g and -lprofiler (google-prof) flags.
- make SEQLIB=false will compile without SeqLib library.
- make LZ4=false will compile without LZ4 library.

If you just call "make", it will compile with : DEBUG=false, SEQLIB=true, LZ4=true

Run options
----------------------
To choose in/out library for SAM/BAM/FASTA files, add the parameter:
- tool=bamtools (default)
- tool=seqlib

To choose compression library, add the parameter:
- compression=zlib (default)
- compression=lz4
- compression=none 
